# This file was generated by Cursor AI on 2026-05-02.
"""
Summarize eqsat benchmark JSON results: per-file min/max/mean/median for numeric
fields; vs control, percent tables, and total absolute reduction sum max(0, control-variant)
per metric; plus n red>0 for scq only in the avg red%>0 table.

Regenerates virtual_best_scq.json (min scq across the five source runs) via
virtual_best.write_virtual_best
before printing tables. Prints a separate table of timeout/memout counts from egglog-status and
gurobi-status (gurobi-encoding: encoding_timeout / encoding_memout; gurobi: solver timeout/memout).
Also prints average num-enodes and num-eclasses per results file (egglog graph size), and one
aggregate over greedy_ac.json, greedy_no_ac.json, ilp_ac.json, and ilp_no_ac.json for whichever
of those files exist: total rows
(``n`` × benchmarks per loaded file), how many rows have both num-enodes and num-eclasses under 100 and
what fraction of all rows that is, plus how many of those small-graph rows had timeout/memout
and what fraction of the small-graph subset that is.

Usage:
    python3 report_results.py [RESULTS_DIR]

Default RESULTS_DIR is this script's directory joined with "results".
"""

